===Noun phrase===
'''[[rite]] of [[passage]]''' (''plural:'' '''rites of passage''')

#''(Anthropology)'' a ceremony or series of ceremonies, often very ritualized, to celebrate a transition in a person’s life. [[Baptism]]s, [[bar mitzvah]]s, [[wedding]]s and [[funeral]]s are among the best known examples.
#:'''Examples:''' After John offically attained his majority, Robert bought him his first legal beer. This is a common American rite of passage.

